args: A short while prior to Pinon and Nevin\nvisiting South Grastaea...
Apostle Pinon reporting.\nWhat are your orders?
Recently, we've received multiple reports\nof an informer in our ranks who has been\nleaking classified information.
I have heard similar rumors.\nThe dissident, right?
Indeed. Our intelligence network has\ntracked this individual to a town called\nMuskov in the Osborne Principality.
I want you to track them down\nand deal with the situation.
And who will I be reporting to?
This mission is yours alone, Apostle Pinon.\nYou also need not await Gabriel's return.
You mean you're...giving me\na solo assignment?
I did not stutter. Now hurry to the site\nand see that Her will is done.
I expect great things from you.
By the Goddess... By the Goddess!
No more am I merely a burden on\nmy seniors. I finally have a mission\nof my own!
This must mean my hard work has finally\nbeen recognized. I must ensure I live up \nto Sandalphon's expectations!
Your young apostle is ready for whatever\nchallenges may await her, Gabriel.\nI will make you proud!
If I knew we were doing soliloquies today,\nI would have prepared something.
Yep! Papa Bear is here in all his\nstrong and handsome glory.
Don't use your nonsense to hide the fact\nyou snuck up on me! Such behavior is\nexceedingly rude.
Pretty standard practice on the battlefield\nthough—and your enemies won't give two\nrips if you think they're rude or not.
You've still got a long way to go\nif I need to teach you that.
If you don't shape up, Gabriel's never\ngoing to think she can let go of her\ncute little bunny wabbit, eh?

I'll thank you to keep your opinions of my
parental relations out of your mouth!
You, a man who is laziness incarnate,
has no right to judge me so.
But listen, forget all that. I hear the big\ncheese is sending you out to Osborne?
Well, that just happens to be right in the\nneck of the woods where I'm headed.
Yeah, I just got a mission myself: Some\nstate-of-the-art magical weapon managed\nto walk away from a base.

You know, for a big smarty, you're awfully
slow on the uptake sometimes. This is your
first solo mission, yeah? So this is just me
offering up a little welcome assistance.
Eeep! Er, I mean... That is to say...
Wh-while I appreciate your gesture,\nI simply couldn't ask that of you when I\nwas ordered to pursue the mission alone.
Listen, I get it. You've worked hard for this,\nand the last thing I wanna do is dump a\nbucket of ice water on your big moment.

But if things sound like they're gonna get
rough, make sure you call me right away.
Don't go getting all reckless on your
first flight outta the nest, dig?
Oh, and I'd love to avoid having to deal\nwith any four-alarm fires, so try to keep\neverything on the up-and-up.
Your lethargy would have you avoid\none-alarm fires if you could—but I shall\nstill take your words to heart.
I will not permit you to think of me as a\n＂cute bunny＂ for the rest of your days.
Tsk! Bold words and a brave front for sure.

But she has a habit of not being able to
do her best when she tries too hard.
I hope that need to succeed doesn't trip
her up...
Well, this is Muskov, which means the\ndissident should be here somewhere...
It's a large town with an imposing\ncathedral, just as our intel suggested.
But it's the middle of the day, and I don't\nsee any children or elderly people about.
There's something odd about this place...
